com.cisco.mscviewer.model

Class Interaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cisco.mscviewer.model.Interaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interval, Value

    public final class Interaction
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interval
    an Interaction represents a cause-effect relationship between two Events. Messaging between two entities, initiation and completion of an asynchronous operation in an entity, the instantiation of an entity by another one are all examples of interactions.
    An interaction has a source event (or cause) and a sink event (or effect). sometimes a source file may contain information only about the source or sink for an interaction, in which case the other event for the interaction is null. Note that source and sink event may belong to the same or different entities.
    An interaction has a type and an associated renderer. Interactions are stored in the data model as Intervals in an interval tree http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interval_tree. Elements of the tree must implement the Interval interface, which this class does implement.
